James Webster targeted female shoppers at the Lidl store in Maidenhead , Berkshire , as they hunted for bargains in the large chest freezers .
The 35-year-old was caught after attracting the attention of a fellow shopper , who spotted him moving the bag he was carrying .
Security admitted Webster had cut a hole in the bag through which he placed the lens of a camera so he could face prison .
Webster , ordered him to complete a sexual offences treatment programme .